<FIRST>r i PM-BRF--Poland-Glider     07-06 0175</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Poland-Glider,0179</SECOND>
<HEAD>Soviet Military Plane Hits Glider, Killing Its Pilot</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WARSAW, Poland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Soviet military plane on a training
flight collided with a glider, killing the glider pilot, the
state-run news agency PAP reported.
   The collision occurred Wednesday near the city of Lubin, 290
miles southwest of Warsaw, the agency said, quoting a Defense
Ministry spokesman.
   The PAP report did not name the type of Soviet plane involved and
said its pilot landed safely at his home airport. The agency did not
say where the flight originated.
   ``The reasons for the accident will be investigated by a special
commission with the participation of Polish and Soviet military
experts,'' PAP said.
   On Tuesday, A Soviet MiG-23 jet, also on a training mission, flew
pilotless 560 mile across Europe before crashing into a house in
Belgium, killing a man.
   The pilot of that jet bailed out after takeoff from the Kolobrzeg
airfield in Poland when the plane developed a mechanical problem,
Soviet Defense Minister Dmitri Yazov told the Soviet news agency
Tass on Wednesday.
</TEXT>
