<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--Fireworks-Horoscope     07-06 0139</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Fireworks-Horoscope,0143</SECOND>
<HEAD>Pyrotechnician Ignores Horoscope: Show Must Go On</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AMARILLO, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A pyrotechnician ignored his horoscope
warning and went ahead with a July Fourth fireworks display because
in the best show business tradition, the show must go on.
   Bruce Olson, who works for Western Enterprises of Enid, Okla.,
was contracted to do the annual fireworks display at Dick Bivins
Memorial Stadium.
   His horoscope for Tuesday said: ``Avoid setting off fireworks.''
   Olson, an Aries, paid no heed to the stars and went on with the
show, but not without a hitch. A 6-inch shell fired prematurely,
scattering debris in the firing area and forcing a 10-minute delay.
No one was injured.
   Fortunately, the shell had been kept away from the others. That's
the only thing that kept the show from opening with the grand
finale, Olson said.
</TEXT>
