<HEAD>Woman Charged With Murdering Newborn</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MINEOLA, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman who kept her pregnancy a secret
allegedly killed her newborn son by slashing his throat with a razor
blade after she gave birth in the bathroom of a drug store, police
said Thursday.
   ``She was apparently overwhelmed by the enormity of the
pregnancy,'' said Nassau County police Lt. John Nolan. ``She just
decided she would kill the baby.''
   Christine Forsyth, 21, of Uniondale, gave birth at the drug store
