<FIRST>r i AM-China-Vacations     07-06 0170</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-China-Vacations,0175</SECOND>
<HEAD>Government Cancels Summer Vacations For All Officials</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-China, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   China's government and Communist Party officials
face a long summer.
   Their summer vacations have been canceled by order of the party
Central Committee and the State Council, China's cabinet, the
official Xinhua News Agency said Thursday.
   The order, which Xinhua described as ``an urgent announcement,''
was made ``to promote hard work and plain living, and recover the
losses caused by the recent turmoil and counterrevolutionary
rebellion.''
   Chinese from all walks of life participated in the seven-week
movement for democracy. Factory production dropped and other
business operations were interrupted as employees in Beijing and
other large cities took to the streets.
   The order said party and government employees at every level
would be affected, and the only holidays to be taken are those set
by the state.
   Work units were ordered not to give compensation, in money or
goods, for the lost vacations, and those who violate the order will
be disciplined, the order said.
</TEXT>
