<FIRST>r w AM-MarilynQuayle     07-06 0114</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Marilyn Quayle,100</SECOND>
<HEAD>Vice President's Wife Sprains Ankle</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Marilyn Quayle, the wife of Vice President Dan
Quayle, sprained her ankle over the July 4 holiday while playing
volleyball with her children at Camp David, her spokeswoman said.
   Mrs. Quayle was going for a point and collided with one of her
sons, said her spokeswoman, Denise Balzano.
   ``He got up and she didn't,'' the spokeswoman said.
   Mrs. Quayle was taken to a hospital in Hagerstown, Md., near the
presidential retreat, to have her ankle X-rayed.
   She was not admitted, however, and was up and around, walking
unassisted into a White House ceremony for the Presidential Medal of
Freedom winners on Thursday.
</TEXT>
