<HEAD>Spanish Composer Ernesto Halffter Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MADRID, Spain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Spanish composer Ernesto Halffter was buried
at Madrid Almudena Cemetery on Thursday after his death at age 84
from heart failure, his son Manuel said.
   Halffter died at his Madrid home on Wednesday, his son added.
   One of his most popular works was the ballet ``Sonatina y
Sinfonetta,'' which premiered in Buenos Aires, Argentina, in 1929.
   At age 19, Halffter began his music studies in Granada with
Spanish composer Manuel de Falla.
   De Falla died in 1946. Halffter completed de Falla's unfinished
symphony ``La Atlantidad,'' which won critical acclaim at its
premiere in Barcelona, Spain, in 1961.
