<FIRST>r a AM-BRF--MinutemanTest     07-06 0116</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Minuteman Test,0118</SECOND>
<HEAD>Air Force Test Launches Minuteman III Missile</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VANDENBERG AIR FORCE BASE, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An Air Force test of an
unarmed Minuteman III missile was successfully completed over the
Pacific Ocean on Thursday, military officials said.
   The missile was launched at 6:16 a.m. and traveled 4,200 miles
across the ocean, splashing down at the Kwajalein Missile Range in
the Marshall Islands about half an hour later, the 4392nd Aerospace
Support Wing of the Strategic Air Command said in a statement.
   The SAC wing is based at Vandenberg Air Force Base.
   Thursday's launch was the 476th SAC operational test launch of a
Minuteman missile, and the 138th of the Minuteman III from
Vandenberg.
</TEXT>
