<FIRST>r f BC-Vestron     07-06 0106</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Vestron,0113</SECOND>
<HEAD>Report: Troubled Movie Company Failed to Make Loan Payment</HEAD>
<DATELINE>STAMFORD, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Vestron Inc. officials declined to comment
Thursday on a published report that the troubled movie company
failed to make payment on a $25 million loan.
   The Advocate newspaper of Stamford reported that Vestron failed
to make the payment, due July 3, to Wells Fargo bank.
   The newspaper said its information came from sources who asked
not to be identified.
   Vestron, based in Stamford, dismissed 140 employees last week as
a cost-cutting move. Vestron produces motion pictures and
distributes videos.
   The company's only hit movie was the 1987 release ``Dirty
Dancing.''
</TEXT>
